                    </div>
                    <span>The text of this book could be reduced to 20% its original size if the author addressed the reader as a competent, intelligent manager. Instead, it's filled with cute pictures and 'how to's' I've heard the GE Way is good; don't opt for the Fieldbook.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The Jack Welch Way is the Only Way</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>6</span>
                      /
                      <span>9</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-03-09</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I have read everything that has ever been written about the golden boy of corporate america - Jack Welch.  He is a genious for our times and this book is just another example of his legendary managerial style.  An easy read that is filled with key information to turn any company into an industry leader and any manager into a corporate leader.  This book details everything a manager will ever need to know.  A MUST BUY !!!!!!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Microsoft Reader makes this title a mistake</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
